               <p>MR. PHILLIPS conducted the prosecution.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18280529-250-person1351">
                  DANIEL 
                  FORRESTER
               <interp inst="t18280529-250-person1351" type="surname" value="FORRESTER"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280529-250-person1351" type="given" value="DANIEL"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280529-250-person1351" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am an officer. On the evening of the 22d of April, I watched Mr. Clark's warehouse, and saw the prisoner come out; I followed him down <placeName id="t18280529-250-crimeloc1380">East Smithfield</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18280529-250-crimeloc1380" type="placeName" value="East Smithfield"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18280529-250-crimeloc1380" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18280529-250-off1378 t18280529-250-crimeloc1380"></join>, where he joined a woman, and went into a liquor-shop; I followed him, pulled off his hat, and found these two pieces of calico - he said, "You don't mean to take me for this, we will have a drop of something to drink; you don't know me, nor I you;" I took him to his master's counting-house, and he said, he took it to make a pair of drawers - he said this quite voluntarily.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18280529-250-person1352">
                  ROBERT 
                  BYFIELD
               <interp inst="t18280529-250-person1352" type="surname" value="BYFIELD"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280529-250-person1352" type="given" value="ROBERT"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280529-250-person1352" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am in Mr. John Clark's employ. The prisoner was brought back in custody; I did not see him until next morning - I saw the goods safe at four o'clock.(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18280529-250-person1353">
                  HENRY 
                  PHILLIPS
               <interp inst="t18280529-250-person1353" type="surname" value="PHILLIPS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280529-250-person1353" type="given" value="HENRY"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280529-250-person1353" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am in Mr. Clark's employ, and was present when the prisoner was brought back; no threat or inducement was held out to him - he said, "It is only a piece of brown cotton, which I took to make myself a pair of drawers;" the officer said, "Then you acknowledge you had it from Mr. Clark's?" he said, Yes; he has been in our employ one year and three quarters.</p>
               <p>
